  "instructions": [
    "Heat olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add onions and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.",
    "Stir in garlic, smoked paprika, lemon juice, vinegar, tomato paste, salt, and water. Bring to a boil.",
    "Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for about 10 minutes or until lentils are tender.",
    "Add pickled vegetables and cook for an additional 2-3 minutes.",
    "Garnish with lemon zest before serving.",
    "Serve hot as a side dish or over rice."
